Jenni Evans Western Cape traffic authorities had their hands full on Wednesday when a rockfall led to the closure of Chapman's Peak Drive, and parts of the N1 near De Doorns and Worcester were closed due to two truck accidents. According to provincial traffic chief Kenny Africa, one truck crashed on the N1 near De Doorns on Wednesday morning. Read:Â Fleeing motorist plunges down Chapman's Peak Drive in early morning crash In the crash, between Sandhills and Orchards, the truck straddled the road and part of it was over the middle barrier. Motorists were advised to take alternate routes.    In the second accident, a truck overturned on the N1, about 5km from Worcester on the Touws River side. Two occupants were slightly injured. Authorities put in place a stop-go system to enable motorists to skirt the accident. The scenic Chapman's Peak Drive was also closed on Wednesday morning, due to a rockfall. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  